#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Kulagharaṇīsutta"
msgstr "8. The Mistress of the House"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time one of the monks was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a "
"certain forest grove."

msgctxt "sn9.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu aññatarasmiṃ kule ativelaṃ "
"ajjhogāḷhappatto viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time that monk had become too closely involved in that family’s "
"affairs."

msgctxt "sn9.8:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā "
"atthakāmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ saṃvejetukāmā yā tasmiṃ kule kulagharaṇī, tassā "
"vaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ "
"bhikkhuṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest had compassion for that monk, wanting what’s "
"best for him. So, wanting to stir him up, they manifested in the appearance "
"of the mistress of that family, approached the monk, and addressed him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.8:2.1"
msgid "“Nadītīresu saṇṭhāne,"
msgstr "“On the banks of the rivers and in the guest houses,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:2.2"
msgid "sabhāsu rathiyāsu ca;"
msgstr "in meeting halls and highways,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:2.3"
msgid "Janā saṅgamma mantenti,"
msgstr "people come together and gossip:"

#. <br>
#. VAR: tañca → tvañca (mr)
msgctxt "sn9.8:2.4"
msgid "mañca tañca kimantaran”ti."
msgstr "what’s going on between you and me?”"

# See http://sanskritdictionary.com/?iencoding=iast&q=praty%C5%ABha&lang=sans&action=Search
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.434"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.8:3.1"
msgid "“Bahūhi saddā paccūhā,"
msgstr "“There’s lots of annoying sounds"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:3.2"
msgid "khamitabbā tapassinā;"
msgstr "that an austere ascetic must endure."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:3.3"
msgid "Na tena maṅku hotabbaṃ,"
msgstr "But they mustn’t be dismayed by that,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:3.4"
msgid "na hi tena kilissati."
msgstr "for that’s not what defiles you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.8:4.1"
msgid "Yo ca saddaparittāsī,"
msgstr "If you’re startled by every little sound,"

# vatamiga is evidently a mythical beast renowned for its flightiness; it only occurs in Ja 14 and Tha-ap 482, both in legendary stories of the past.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:4.2"
msgid "vane vātamigo yathā;"
msgstr "like a wind-deer in the wood,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:4.3"
msgid "Lahucittoti taṃ āhu,"
msgstr "they’ll call you ‘flighty minded’;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.8:4.4"
msgid "nāssa sampajjate vatan”ti."
msgstr "and your practice won’t succeed.”"
